4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE USE OF THE EMPLOYMENT SECURITY
5 ACCOUNT; TRANSFERRING THE OFFICE OF COMMUNITY SERVICE TO THE DEPARTMENT OF LABOR
6 AND INDUSTRY; AMENDING THE EMPLOYMENT SECURITY ACCOUNT TO INCLUDE FUNDING OF THE
7 OFFICE OF COMMUNITY SERVICE AND COMMISSION FOR HUMAN RIGHTS AS AN ALLOWABLE USE;
8 AND AMENDING SECTIONS 39-51-409 AND 90-14-103, MCA.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 39-51-409, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "39-51-409. Employment security account. (1) There is an account in the state special revenue
14 fund called the employment security account.
15 (2) Money deposited in the employment security account may be appropriated to the department
16 for payment of:
17 (a) unemployment insurance benefits;
18 (b) expenses incurred in the administration of the unemployment insurance program;
19 (c) expenses incurred in collecting money deposited in the account;
20 (d) expenses incurred for the employment offices established in 39-51-307, including expenses for
21 providing services to the business community;
22 (e) expenses incurred for the apprenticeship and training program and for the administration of 39-
23 71-319;
24 (f) expenses for displaced homemaker programs provided for under 39-7-305;
25 (g) expenses for department research and analysis functions that provide employment, wage, and
26 economic data;
27 (h) expenses for department functions pertaining to wage and hour laws, prevailing wages, and
28 collective bargaining; and
