16 Section 2. Section 90-14-103, MCA, is amended to read:
17 "90-14-103. Office of community service. (1) There is an office of community service, which is
18 headed by a director and established in the office of the governor department of labor and industry.
19 (2) The purpose of this office is to:
20 (a) renew the ethic of civic responsibility in the state;
21 (b) encourage the citizens of the state, regardless of age or income, to engage in full-time or part-
22 time service to the state;
23 (c) call young people to serve in projects that will benefit the state and improve their life chances
24 through the acquisition of literacy, job skills, and interpersonal skills;
25 (d) build on the existing organizational framework of state and local governmental entities to
26 expand full-time and part-time service opportunities in a wide variety of programs for all citizens, particularly
27 youth and older Montanans;
28 (e) involve participants in activities that would not otherwise be performed by employed workers;
